@DbDefaultValue() attribute Annotation.description: The default value in the database.

@DbName() attribute Annotation.description: The name in the database (for example the column name in a relational database)

@DbType() attribute Annotation.description: The attribute type in the database (for example the column type in a relational database)

@DefaultValue() attribute Annotation.description: The default value for an attribute

@Embedded link Annotation.description:
The entity referenced by the attribute must be embedded (typically for NoSQL databases).
Applicable with "references" to embed them in the current entity.

@FetchTypeEager link Annotation.description: Define an "Eager Loading" fetch type for a link, typically for ORM (JPA, Doctrine, etc ).

@FetchTypeLazy link Annotation.description: Define an "Lazy Loading" fetch type for a link, typically for ORM (JPA, Doctrine, etc ).
